-- 
African Development Bank Approves $96.6 Million Mozambique Loan

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-09-23T02:27:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/african-development-bank-approves-96-6-million-mozambique-loan.html
The  African Development Bank  has
approved a $96.6 million loan to  Mozambique  to finance the
country’s Growth and Public sector Efficiency Programme (GPSE),
the bank said today in a statement on its website.  The funds are designed to assist Mozambique to “broaden
the social impacts of the country’s robust economic growth on
effective  job creation , income generation and poverty
reduction,” the lender said.  The GPSE, which will be implemented over three fiscal
years, will improve the business environment and employment
creation through access to credit for small scale enterprises
and improve public sector efficiency and transparency, the
lender said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
